urls.title: Twiddler's syndrome
urls.description: A 52-year-old woman came for evaluation of an abnormal remote device transmission 3 weeks after implantation of a dual-chamber pacemaker. She described right-sided thumping discomfort in her chest. Upon device testing, the ventricular pacing threshold was unattainable with failure to capture. Her chest discomfort resolved immediately after the ventricular lead amplitude was decreased, suggesting lead dislodgement and ectopic stimulation. Chest radiograph (figure) showed 270° rotation of the generator, causing retraction of leads to the cavoatrial junction.

tweets.text:
